This project automatically posts daily updates about the U.S. national debt using official Treasury data from the **Debt to the Penny API**.

Each day, it:
1. Fetches the most recent total U.S. public debt value from the [FiscalData Treasury API](https://fiscaldata.treasury.gov/datasets/debt-to-the-penny).
2. Compares it with values from the previous business day and the same day one week earlier.
3. Calculates **daily** and **weekly** increases.
4. Formats a tweet with the new figures.
5. Posts automatically to X (Twitter) via the X API.

